title: 820-00840 No PP3V3_G3H
message:
Hi there. I have an 820-00840. No power. Stuck at 5v and 0A from charger. There was some corrosion around CD3215's so I replaced with brand new ones (from your store) as well as ISL9239 (new) and U6990.

PPVIN _G3H is 5V going into U6990 but there is no PM_EN_P3V3_G3H coming from ISL9239 even after replacing.

Where do I go from here?

title: 820-00840 No PP3V3_G3H
message: Post diode mode to ground at L6995 and F7000.

title: 820-00840 No PP3V3_G3H
message: PS there is no short to ground on PP3V3_G3H

U7000 has been replaced again (NEW), as well as another set of CD3215's (NEW) as well as U6990 (NEW). 5.19V on the charger pulling 40 milliamps.

PP3V3_G3H is 4.25V now. What would be causing this overvoltage? Where should I look next?

title: 820-00840 No PP3V3_G3H
message:
So now you get 5V at  PM_EN_P3V3_G3H?

Corroded resistor on R6993-97 divider, will change 3V3_G3H voltage.
R6995/97 went high, or R6993/96 decreased values.
